{
  "stem": "15962.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they told me that I should go to school as usual and that the Germans are moving into town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that same day, we learned that my father's sister, who was an elderly lady, lived right on the main square of this little town where the Germans stopped to rest the, the troops.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was snowing lightly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was very a kind of a cold, damp morning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I heard that my aunt came down and gave the soldiers some hot tea or hot coffee.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And a few hours later, she poisoned herself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She took her own life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So she was the first victim and also the first funeral that I attended and maybe the only one, because there were no funerals thereafter.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was the first time that I went to the new cemetery that was open only a year or so and participated and at the services.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things gradually changed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every few weeks, there would be a new proclamation, new laws, new regulations, that would restrict our lives.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The restrictions would primarily apply to Jews, less so to the general population.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Jews were not allowed to have bicycles and fur coats and silverware and watches and gold.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father first could only treat-- well, first, his, his insurance company informed him that he can no longer treat patients for the state insurance company, which was probably at least 50% of his practice.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He then was not allowed to treat non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And eventually, he had to completely close his office.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jews were not allowed to go out after eight o'clock.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were not allowed to go to some places of public meetings, [INAUDIBLE] parks, coffee houses, restaurants.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were only few designated places where they could eat or shop.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
